The groups will be assigned a day to share their traditions with the class. They will be asked to bring in props, food, and to teach us some of the language. text: Hate to be negative but "WTF".  I watched this, as the first film, whilst not particularly good" the soundtrack and musical content carried it from beginning to end and I ended up smiling and enjoying.  Expecting the same, I actually paid to watch this, so called "entertainment" and I use the word reservedly, rather than sit at home and give Mr Smirnoff a damn good thrashing. It turned out that I was not just disappointed but highly envious of the writers, the producers and the director for being paid copious amounts of money to perform a job that they are clearly lacking in talent for.  The general public have been conned into spending what might be a considerable amount of their hard earned money on a film that they will be able to pick up in a local charity shop for pennies 2 weeks after it is released on DVD.   I do not blame the actors as they have to work with what they are given and, they were given nothing. I appreciate that there is a more appropriate web site for my comments but I've forgotten my password. :-)
